verbs.description: wrawl (third-person singular simple present wrawls, present participle wrawling, simple past and past participle wrawled)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, intransitive) To cry like a cat; to waul.
examples: The fog horns groaned and groaned again, and siren whistled and wrawled.
